Adapted dependencies in pom.xml (newer versions of cqengine, kubernetes-client and kubernetes-server-mock) to reduce warnings in build:

spring-boot-starter-parent, version 2.2.7 RELEASE has now a different location in the artifactory (release instead of lib-release): https://repo.spring.io/webapp/#/artifacts/browse/tree/General/release/org/springframework/boot/spring-boot-starter-parent
kubernetes-client and kubernetes-server-mock have dependencies to sundr-codegen which causes the build to display these warnings:

The POM for io.sundr:sundr-codegen:jar:0.13.1 is invalid, transitive dependencies (if any) will not be available: 2 problems were encountered while building the effective model for io.sundr:sundr-codegen:0.13.1
The POM for io.sundr:sundr-codegen:jar:0.21.0 is invalid, transitive dependencies (if any) will not be available: 1 problem was encountered while building the effective model for io.sundr:sundr-codegen:0.21.0

The second one could be resolved by upgrading the version of the kubernetes libraries.

cqengine relies on libraries that rely on older versions of Java (<11). This results in a warning, again resulting from javassis-3.25-GA trying to access com.sun.:tools. Unfortunately upgrading the version does not resolve this issue. See also https://stackoverflow.com/a/60549167.

Resolved error for running the build with JDK 13 (target is still 11) due to generic type resolution by a library used by cqengine that caused the build to fail due to failing tests.. The fix is to not use anonymous method references or lambdas in methods that call net.jodah.typetools.TypeResolver:
 /**
     * The {@link com.googlecode.cqengine.query.QueryFactory#attribute(String, SimpleFunction)})} relies on a method
     * {@link net.jodah.typetools.TypeResolver#resolveRawArguments(Type, Class)}, which in Java 13 is not able to retrieve
     * information about the generic types, if a lambda or anonymous method reference is provided. By providing an anonymous
     * class of the {@link SimpleFunction}, the generic types can be resolved without running into exceptions.
     */
    @SuppressWarnings({"Convert2Lambda", "Anonymous2MethodRef"})
    private static final Attribute<Item, String> IDENTIFIER = attribute("identifier", new SimpleFunction<>() {
        @Override
        public String apply(Item item) {
            return item.getIdentifier();
        }
    });
Adapted readme.md for Windows Docker support.
Added test steps to CI for JDK 11 and 13 on all OS
